dataIdInfo.envirDesc: Microsoft Windows 7 Version 6.1 (Build 7601) Service Pack 1; Esri ArcGIS 10.1.0.3035
dataIdInfo.idPurp: Display the Virginia Department of Environmental Quality’s (DEQ) Regional Office assessment responsibilities per 6th order (HUC12) unit of the National Watershed Boundary Dataset using the July 2016 (version 5) release. DEQ dissolved the Lynchburg office effective May 1, 2017 therefore adjacent offices assumed the assessment of the watersheds formerly assigned to the Lynchburg office.
dataIdInfo.idAbs: Per the dissolution of the South Central Regional Office in November 2008, the Blue Ridge Regional Office was created whereby the one region maintained 2 offices – Blue Ridge-Roanoke and Blue Ridge-Lynchburg, as well as their pre-existing assessment responsibilities. Effective May 2017, the Blue Ridge-Lynchburg office is dissolved and Roanoke is the operational location of the Blue Ridge Regional Office. Assessment responsibilities from the former Lynchburg office were reassigned to adjacent regions to maintain continuity of our monitoring and assessment network. This dataset contains the Assessment Region and Office Name assigned to each of the 1,251 6th order units of version 5 of Virginia's portion of the National Watershed Boundary Dataset.
dataIdInfo.idCredit: Virginia Department of Environmental Quality, VA DEQ

Consts.useLimit: This dataset was created using the Department of Conservation and Recreation's (DCR) NWBD v5 data release and DEQ's watershed network assessment decisions. Use of this custom dataset should recognize the resource creators. Use and distribution is not prohibited.

report.measDesc: The map and data only includes information relative to which 6th order (HUC12) watersheds correspond to which regional office within Virginia’s jurisdictional limits. Ancillary data is from the original master12_v5 table provided with the file geodatabase containing all 6th order watersheds within and that cross Virginia's state boundary.

dataSource.srcDesc: Features are derived from VaNWBD6v5.gdb from DCR's website (http://www.dcr.virginia.gov/soil-and-water/hu) downloaded August 2016.

prcStep.stepDesc: Download VaNWBDv5 geodatabase file from DCR's hydrologic unit geography webpage.
Export file geodatabase (VaNWBD6v5.gdb) as personal geodatabase and rename to AssessmentRegions_VA.mdb.
Add field names ASSESS_REG and OFFICE_NM to AssessmentRegions_VA table.
Join master12_v5 table to AssessmentRegions_VA table.
Queried for and merged duplicate VAHU6 polygons into single multipart polygon.
Add VAHU5 as a field name and update each record based on version 4 of the NWBD.
Assign values to ASSESS_REG and OFFICE_NM based on NRO/PRO/VRO decisions of reassignment of former BRRO-Lynchburg office watersheds to each region.
Assign values to remaining Null values in ASSESS_REG and OFFICE_NM based on pre-existing assessment responsibilities across the state.
Export final product in map format as PDF and PNG for use in 2016 Integrated Report.
Export AssessmentRegions_VA personal geodatabase feature class as shapefile to share with staff on network drive.

Update VAHU5 codes for the 4 new VAHU6 codes with one DEQ modification. NE-z was changed to NE-0 to avoid a duplication error when querying for the number of unique VAHU5 codes. Use of a number instead of a letter is not approved by DCR but necessary to avoid possible errors if an application is not able to distinguish a difference between NE-Z and NE-z.
